[http://rosewill.com/Mgnt/Uploads2/AttachmentForProduct/20120803_l600n-usermanual.pdf Manual] {{TechInfoDepot|Rosewill_L600N}} Per Rosewill, this device uses a '''Broadcom''' SoC (says BCM5358), has 8MB Flash, and has 64MB RAM.
Per the manual, the device uses BCM5358U (presumed B0 rev.) and BCM43236. However, the manual states the device has 32MB RAM.. Per the manual, the default SSIDs are '''RW-2.4G-XXX''' and '''RW-5G-XXX'''. The MAC label on the board in the FCC internal photos may have an OUI of 00:1F:A4 ('''Shenzhen Gongjin Electronics'''). :There are some entries for the '''RX-2.4G-XXX''' pattern on '''WiGLE''' (all '''RW-2.4G-001'''). There is a single '''RW-5G-001''' entry as well, but the BSSID may be bogus... ==Additional external links== *[http://www.dd-wrt.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?p=757665 ''Rosewill L600N support?'' on the '''DD-WRT Forum'''] *[http://repo.or.cz/w/tomato.git/commit/c5189140fa758c447b6638695745ff5924e122a7 Commit adding ''untested'' support to '''''Shibby''''''s '''Tomato''' builds] (and allowing for [http://tomato.groov.pl/tomatoanon.php '''TomatoAnon''' model detection] ==Images== File:Rosewill L600N 1.jpg|angled File:Rosewill L600N 2.jpg|back File:Rosewill L600N 3.jpg|side File:Rosewill L600N 4.jpg|back, on stand [[Has images::external| ]]
